							  <h1>BOMARKET, Seoul Forest</h1>
								<a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/3ezkqXovnRfhpV3N9" target="_blank">
								  B1, 83-21, Wangsimni-ro, Seongdong-gu, Seoul, South Korea
								</a>
								<p></p>
							  <p><strong>Living Concept Store &amp; Brunch Café</strong></p>

							  <p>
								BOMARKET is not just a lifestyle store — it’s more like a <em>“cultural curation market.”</em>
								From living goods and imported groceries to kitchenware, wine, and brunch, it’s a thoughtfully composed space filled with delightful details and eye-catching products.
								Especially notable are the beautifully designed items — you’ll be drawn in first by the aesthetics before anything else.
							  </p>

							  <p>
								The interior design is just as impressive. Pastel tones and mint hues set the mood, with large windows that let in natural light. 
								The layout makes it easy to enjoy browsing, brunching, and relaxing with coffee all in one visit.
								It’s also pet-friendly, so many people come with their dogs, adding to the warm, relaxed atmosphere.
							  </p>

							  <p>At BOMARKET, you can enjoy a wide range of experiences:</p>
								<ul>
								  <li>Brunch &amp; Light Meals: Kimchi fried rice, rosé tteokbokki, poke, salad pasta — healthy and affordable.</li>
								  <li>Drinks: Specialty coffee, lattes, herbal teas, refreshing seasonal beverages.</li>
								  <li>Shopping: Tableware, imported snacks, kitchen goods, wine, stationery, and lifestyle products with unique design.</li>
								  <li>Gifting: Wine, aesthetic goods, and other thoughtfully curated items.</li>
								</ul>
							  

							  <p>The D-Tower Street building where BOMARKET is located is surrounded by charming shops and great places to eat — perfect for a slow stroll. One place worth checking out is a bakery café called 'REBREAD'. <br>
							If you’re planning to explore the Seongsu area, I definitely recommend including this stop on your itinerary.</p>

							  <p>
								What makes BOMARKET special is the blend of <em>“food, curated shopping, and atmosphere”</em> — all in one place.
								It’s not just a brunch café or a concept store. It’s a stay-a-while destination that feels both relaxing and inspiring.
							  </p>
